{"title":"AMS Meets Red Bull Rampage With Two New Mountain Bike Grips","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/02/ams-red-bull-rampage-grips/","date":1635861650000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div data-off-canvas-content=\"\"><main><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></main><main role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276851\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The Red Bull Rampage is one of the freeride mountain bike world’s premier events. Now, component brand AMS has teamed up with Rampage to produce a pair of branded grips that bring the energy and verve of the Utah desert to your home mountain.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1.jpg\" alt=\"amx rampage grips on a white background\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31160927/ams-rampage-grips-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The Cero and Berm both come in black with a bronze-colored collar emblazoned with the Red Bull Rampage logo in white.</p><h2>Cero Grips<a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1.jpg\"><br><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161031/ams-rampage-grips-4-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></h2><p>The Cero grips feature a two-pattern design—large inward-facing diamonds at the thumb and outward-facing, smaller diamonds around the rest of the grip, with a waffle pattern on the bottom side. There’s just the hint of a flange at the end. The Cero grips will cost you $35.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3.jpg\" alt=\"amx rampage grips on a white background\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161108/ams-rampage-grips-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Here are the specs:</p><ul><li>132mm total length</li><li>30mm constant diameter</li><li>Constant thickness</li><li>94 grams (3.46 ounces)</li></ul><h2>Berm Grips</h2><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161339/ams-rampage-grips-8.jpg\" alt=\"amx rampage grips on a white background\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161339/ams-rampage-grips-8.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161339/ams-rampage-grips-8-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161339/ams-rampage-grips-8-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161339/ams-rampage-grips-8-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161339/ams-rampage-grips-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161339/ams-rampage-grips-8-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></p><p>The Berm grips are a little cheaper at $30. They sport a tapered diameter—thick on the outside and thinner towards the inside. The pattern is uniformly small diamonds, overlaid by waffle ridges on the underside.<a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7.jpg\" alt=\"amx rampage grips on a white background\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/31161138/ams-rampage-grips-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>Check the specs:</p><ul><li>135mm total length</li><li>29.5mm inside. 33.9mm outside diameter</li><li>102 grams (3.6 ounces</li></ul><p>Both pairs of grips lock with a single inside collar and come with free returns and a lifetime warranty. This video from Redbull doesn’t actually feature many close-ups of either style but does have some fun riding, so enjoy!</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"YouTube video player\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AilkIdqOdJ8\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p><p><a href=\"https://www.allmountainstyle.com/\">allmountainstyle.com</a></p></section></article></main></div></div>","author":"Andrew Marshall","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3da074eee22014ae667fafb1da01d4c2c655fedbd6518df01b853b0e3c44cc0a","category":"Cycling"}